&lt;li&gt;Experience with EDR, vulnerability scanners, SIEMs, MDM(Jamf/NinjaOne)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in the following: macOS, Linux, Windows, Google Workspace, Okta, Crowdstrike&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate with internal and external stakeholders while prioritizing tasks and work independently under minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in a 24/7 on-call rotation performing security incident response&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with EDR, vulnerability scanners, SIEMs, MDM, and other common security tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of cloud security best practices and authentication standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of operating system internals, and a core competency in one of the following: Identity and Access, Infrastructure Hardening (macOS, Windows, Linux, ChromeOS), Saas Security and Assurance and validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid hands-on experience with Okta administration, workflows, and identity management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at mentoring, simplifying technical concepts for non-technical audiences, and influencing decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the following Corpsec domains: Corporate Identity, Endpoint Security, Data Loss Prevention, Device Trust, SaaS Security, Zero Trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills for collaborating with diverse teams and translating intricate safety concepts into practical strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
