&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Director for Government Affairs based in Germany who can directly and fully engage in the German policy, budget, and legislative environments. The position will support both national security and civil government interactions and opportunities.&amp;nbsp; The Director of Government Affairs executes Planet’s government affairs strategy across German federal institutions and selected European stakeholders. The role is responsible for shaping engagement, surfacing political risk and opportunity, and ensuring coherent positioning across Planet. Strategic positions, escalation decisions, and external commitments are defined in coordination with Planet leadership and relevant program owners. This role does not carry independent commercial or program accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will interact directly with Members of the Bundestag, the Chancellor’s office, Federal Ministers, and policy shapers at the national level in Germany.&amp;nbsp; The position will attend conferences and symposia and engage in relevant meetings with stakeholders and government officials.&amp;nbsp; The right person for Planet knows how to navigate the complex relationships of the German Federal Government, including the Bundestag and relevant Federal ministries (including the Ministry of Defence and the Ministry of Research, Technology, and Space); has professional experience working with these institutions and detailed knowledge of their processes; and, knows how Planet’s unique capabilities - our agile approach to space technology and our online delivery of a first-of-its-kind data set - meet the requirements and needs of Germany for both national security and civil society.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also support Planet’s efforts to monitor and influence policy and budget environments for the EU, European Commission, ESA, and other relevant European entities.&amp;nbsp; The position will influence the European conversation primarily through partnerships with the German EU delegation and interest groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires close coordination with both internal and external constituencies, and the ability to communicate and collaborate effectively with Planet’s customers, potential government funders, NGOs, technical partners and team members around the world, in a highly-dynamic, high-growth commercial company. Planet’s services are novel, and thus we are looking for someone to simultaneously educate stakeholders on the broader context of the commercial aerospace opportunities while also specifically understanding short-term opportunities for Planet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, hybrid role which will require you to work from our Berlin office 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You’ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate thought leadership in the German policy community—both in the national security and civil society space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support engagements with the EU, ESA, and European Commission (primarily through the German national delegation) to shape policy and funding opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate Planet’s unique value proposition to the German audience in terms of greatest relevance to that audience, with the ability to design and synthesize new kinds of analysis rather than copy existing approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and collaborate with Planet’s government affairs, business development, and sales teams to develop approaches to capture new opportunities in the German ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a senior advisor and execution partner to sales, program, and regional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Success in this role will result (and be measured) in increased trust and credibility with priority German government stakeholders, early identification and escalation of political risk before it impacts Planet’s business, and consistent, aligned external positioning across Planet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and recent experience in Berlin with German federal institutions, including but not limited to: Bundestag, Chancellor’s Office, Ministry of Defence, the Ministry of Research, Technology, and Space, and other relevant federal ministries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience succeeding in the private and public sector in Germany&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project, time, and budget management skills, and being able to handle multiple tasks simultaneously without sacrificing attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding communication (fluent in both spoken and written German and English), interpersonal, and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work both collaboratively and independently in a high-growth, commercial company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work closely with organizations in a wide variety of sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in lobby work and association working groups&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to meet with members of Government around Berlin up to 5 days per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and recent experience in the EU and its institutions (European Commission etc.), ESA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and recent experience working on space/data policy and/or national security technology policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in drafting position papers&lt;/li&gt;
