&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Pre-Sales will be responsible for leading Pre-Sales Solution Architects in the EMEA region, providing leadership excellence in technical sales, account planning and strategy, relationship building, and solution selling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mission of Pre-Sales is to provide trusted technical advice, enabling customers to maximize their investment in Earth Observation and achieve better outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be an accomplished people manager, a geospatial expert with strong business acumen, and possess proven experience scaling high performing technical teams and implementing technical sales best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a visible, strategic, and influential role, partnering with internal Civil Government &amp;amp; Commercial sales teams, and authorized resellers, to secure sales in new and existing accounts. This person will be a driven, independent thinker and embody a growth mindset, characterized by continuous curiosity, agility and adaptability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, remote position based in Germany, the Netherlands, or the United Kingdom. If located near an office, you are expected to work from that office 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You’ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create the conditions for high performance; recruit resources, define staff learning and development areas, and provide ongoing feedback, coaching and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal sales teams and authorized partners providing quality technical sales capacity and capability to drive revenue in new and existing accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive best practice with emphasis on customer centricity, sales excellence and consultative selling, outcome focus, and data driven decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply expertise in remote sensing and geospatial technologies to develop trusted customer relationships and help them successfully adopt Planet solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high quality customer engagement including meetings, presentations and demonstrations, commercial proposals writing, workshops, pilots, and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with the EMEA Services Director to conduct technical assessments and deliver successful projects that exceed customer expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide customer insights and feedback to product development and marketing organizations, to improve customer engagement, and drive sales revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish global relationships with peers in other Geos to share best practices and drive high standards and execution excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a member of the Global Pre-Sales &amp;amp; Services leadership team and actively contribute to strategic planning, meetings and to execute team initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience managing a successful technical sales team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience working in software or technical sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid technical fluency with system architectures, cloud environments, complex data pipelines, and technical proposal writing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively engage customers at the executive level to clearly articulate technical complexity and strategic business value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consultative selling experience with a proven track record of success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer centric and data-driven, able to turn insights into meaningful actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent human skills: organizer and prioritizer, problem-solver, assertive and proactive, curious and adaptable, communicator and presenter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to partner with Product, Marketing, and Sales leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Management, GIS/Remote Sensing, or comparable combination of technical education and relevant work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic leadership and commercial acumen: ability to manage teams selling complex solutions to governments and/or large enterprise customers, demonstrating excellent commercial and business acumen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales methodology expertise: experience working with Sales Qualification frameworks and methodologies e.g., MEDDPICC, Challenger Sales methodology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Geospatial market, industry, and competitor knowledge (highly preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead customer engagements and facilitate workshops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing or working with/in a Professional Services organization or delivering complex consulting services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiation and influencing skills used to align stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with GIS tools (Esri/QGIS), developing applications/scripts (e.g., Python), and utilizing AI for impact in real-world applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
