&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join a dynamic and innovative team at Planet, where you&#39;ll play a pivotal role supporting our FPGA based designs, which are fundamental to the imaging operations of our cutting-edge satellites. This is a unique opportunity to contribute to the development and validation of our new designs and the improvement of our FPGA build tools and testing infrastructure. You&#39;ll collaborate closely with a diverse group of engineers, including electrical, RF, camera, and firmware specialists, to deliver fully validated designs for our satellites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is passionate about Planet&#39;s mission and thrives in a collaborative, fast-paced environment. This role will appeal to candidates who are looking for opportunities to take an organization to the next level and are deeply mission-driven.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, hybrid role which will require you to work from our San Francisco office 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with RTL/EE/SW engineers to bring up new boards in the lab, to validate and debug new releases, and to automate hardware-in-the-loop testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve and build new features for our FPGA tools and infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with manufacturing test engineers to develop production testing flows to ensure our designs perform as expected after launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement FPGA modules under the guidance of senior engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science or similar with 2+ years of experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with writing SystemVerilog for RTL design and verification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with scripting and programming (Python, C++, shell).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., git).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with lab-based debug of electrical systems (e.g., logic analyzers, oscilloscopes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Xilinx Vivado, Vitis, and Versal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in validating hardware/software interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience testing high speed serial protocols including PCIe/NVMe, MIPI, CameraLink, JESD204B, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
