&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team is in charge of planning the tasks and imagery acquisitions of Earth observation satellites. We do so with a small team of highly-skilled engineers from our offices in SF and Berlin and we are currently looking for a highly motivated and proactive Satellite Tasking Engineer to join our operations team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission will be to support day-to-day operations, which includes collection performance analysis, order monitoring, performing feasibility studies and the development of our operational tools.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a self-starter, quick learner, good communicator, and has the ability to switch contexts quickly. You will be working in a close collaborative environment, and will gain first-hand experience in numerous fields related to managing satellite image acquisition planning, geospatial data analysis, tool development and process automation by supporting our operations team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, remote position based in the United States. If located near an office, you are expected to work from that office 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Collection Planning team during operational planning process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare geospatial data, maps and dashboards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run &amp;amp; interpret standard and complex feasibility studies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops, validates and automates&amp;nbsp; operational tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively improve existing processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborates with image quality support, orbits, mission software, space operations, data pipeline and product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of relevant experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software development experience in Python or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven mindset and comfortable with data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound SQL skills, familiar with git / version control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of satellite imagery and remote sensing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter that proactively tackles problems and brings in their own ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a dynamic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player with an ability to learn and collaborate across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in written and spoken English, the language of the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with automation and software development tools (i.e. Jenkins, Bash, Git)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data visualization platforms (e.g., Looker Studio, OMNI, CARTO).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with geospatial software (e.g., QGIS, ArcGIS, GDAL) or libraries (e.g., Shapely, GeoPandas).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
