&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Electrical Engineering team, you will work in a group of dedicated engineers responsible for the design of Planet’s satellites. You will architect and design the power subsystems on our modular satellite bus, and bring-up, validate, and qualify your designs for the space environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, hybrid role which will require you to be in our San Francisco, HQ 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and schematic entry of power subsystems including MPPTs, electronic propulsion PPUs, power regulation and distribution for our fleets of nano and small satellites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversight of PCB layout process for your designs, as well as release of drawings for manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PCBA bring-up, debugging, and functional verification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;With assistance of other teams, qualify design for EMI/EMC compliance, thermal performance, and ensure design can survive the high shock and vibration loads of a rocket launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the manufacturing test engineering team to define a highly automated test procedure for each PCBA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anomaly response and troubleshooting systems for on-orbit spacecraft.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience designing PCBs, with 5 years focused on power electronics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced experience designing high voltage (&amp;gt;500V) switching power converters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with high voltage power component selection, in particular with compound semiconductor technologies (SiC, GaN)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional design experience with mechanical/thermal and packaging constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with analog design, digital design, mixed-signal design (ADCs/DACs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in embedded systems design&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of PCB layout techniques for optimized power and ground routing and EMI mitigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on expertise with EE tools (oscilloscopes, network analyzers, signal generators, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with simulation tools for power electronics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced with Altium Designer for schematic capture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced in Python or other scripting languages to control/automate test equipment (power supplies, solar array simulators, electronic loads)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience specifying or designing custom magnetics and other passives for power electronics circuits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with MPPTs and solar arrays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with electric propulsion systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing for high-reliability aerospace/LEO applications—designing radiation tolerant electronics, vacuum compatible hardware, frequent thermal cycling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
