&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Planet, we launch spacecrafts early and often. From technology demonstrators to operational constellations, exceptional engineers are needed to design, manufacture, test and launch spacecrafts. This role offers a unique opportunity for an engineer to get involved from A to Z in projects pertaining to a wide range of engineering fields, with some design, analysis, hands-on, and operations opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Spacecraft Qualification engineer, you will join a small team of dedicated engineers&amp;nbsp; playing a key role in the advent of several platforms. The ideal candidate is a self-starter, curious and creative, that has a technical understanding of space systems and wants to be involved with hardware and problems solving. To be successful in this role, the candidate should enjoy hands-on work, thrive in ambiguity, and be able to lead their own projects into completion. Coming from a fast paced, aerospace environment, having completed difficult projects while collaborating effectively with other key teams, will be a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, in-office position based in our San Francisco office 5 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop test plans:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand needs and requirements for various satellites components and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author and maintain detailed test plans, procedures and support tools. Ensure compliance with industry standards and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design and validate test fixtures and Ground Support Equipment (GSE):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use 3D CAD software to design test fixtures and GSE equipment. Run structural FEA. Populate 2D drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and assist with procurement, machining, assembly and proofloading operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conduct testing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, &amp;nbsp;coordinate, and lead the execution of environmental test campaigns, especially for TVAC (Thermal Vacuum) and thermal testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform hands-on operations like GSE and instrumentation setup, inspections, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and understand a variety of computer-automated and manual test equipment, including thermal and TVAC chambers, pumps, valves, compressors, heat exchangers, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of equipment and processes to identify failures, anomalies, root causes, and drive issues to resolution, during and after the test.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive measurement and test data analysis:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure data acquisition software and hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and review data using numerical data analysis tools to interpret test results and ensure that the hardware operates as expected. Identify trends, anomalies, and areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implement continuous improvement and process development:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively improve current test set ups, stations and procedures to increase the efficiency and reliability of testing operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, develop and test innovative mechanical solutions and testing methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Document and develop communication:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep detailed notes of tests, specimens and anomalies. Report test results, providing recommendations for design modifications or improvements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop close communication and working relationships with Engineering and Manufacturing teams. Participate in technical reviews, program status meetings, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, Thermal Engineering or Electro-Mechanics/Robotics Engineering.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of relevant work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in environmental test qualification, running and managing test projects with 3+ months of Thermal Vacuum testing experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency defining test strategies, test plans, test procedures, as well as general manufacturing workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of heat transfer principles and thermal management technology. Data analysis skills for evaluating system performance and identifying anomalies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mechanical systems engineering intuition and critical thinking.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in using Solidworks CAD &amp;amp; FEA (simulation) or equivalent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience (portfolio submission encouraged).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work well under pressure while managing competing demands and tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to be self-directed, detail-oriented, and able to develop creative solutions in a dynamic multi-disciplinary environment. Must be a team player able to work in a collaborative team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional travel should be expected as part of testing and integration operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You Stand Out:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in vibration and shock testing. Experience working with test equipment such as power supplies, multimeters, oscilloscopes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in prototyping, rapid iteration and agile processes. Experience in working in a machine shop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and working with DAQs for test article command/control and data gathering; well-versed with the instrumentation, usage, and data consumption from accelerometers, load cells and other DAQ sensors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in automation. Familiarity with Raspberry Pis, Node Red, or Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
