&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Security Engineer, Embedded Software in Planet&#39;s Satellite Security Team (SatSec) you will work on a variety of projects and tasks to secure Planet&#39;s space-related systems. The SatSec team&#39;s mission is to secure Planet&#39;s space related systems to enable Planet&#39;s earth imaging and data solutions mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with other members of the SatSec and Space Systems Engineering teams, especially Flight Software, the FPGA and Mission software teams, as well as Manufacturing and Mission Operations. You will do some development of software security tools and automation, security review of software, and maintenance of systems critical to the SatSec team&#39;s mission. You will work on some projects on your own, and others in collaboration with development and operational teams to ensure the systems satisfy the security and operational goals. The position has a practical security focus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is someone with embedded software development experience, together with some security experience who now wants to make security the focus, while doing software development, security design, security code review, as well as other operational responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, hybrid role which will require you to work from our San Francisco HQ 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing small software security tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security focused code review of satellite and ground based software (using team’s review guidelines)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review of / writing automation to review security test results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security design reviews (once are familiar with the satellite system)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setup and testing launch racks or lab equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running PEN tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining systems critical to the SatSec team&#39;s mission, such as Hardware Security Modules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network traffic analysis&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with some corporate systems as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc duties depending on engineering projects underway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with embedded systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with encryption and cyber security concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of work experience in computer science, software engineering, electrical engineering or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in C and Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with open source tools and frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent technical and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
