&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to Planet. We believe in using space to help life on Earth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet designs, builds, and operates the largest constellation of imaging satellites in history. This constellation delivers an unprecedented dataset of empirical information via a revolutionary cloud-based platform to authoritative figures in commercial, environmental, and humanitarian sectors. We are both a space company and data company all rolled into one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customers and users across the globe use Planet&#39;s data to develop new technologies, drive revenue, power research, and solve our world’s toughest obstacles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we control every component of hardware design, manufacturing, data processing, and software engineering, our office is a truly inspiring mix of experts from a variety of domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a people-centric approach toward culture and community and we strive to iterate in a way that puts our team members first and prepares our company for growth. Join Planet and be a part of our mission to change the way people see the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planet is a global company with employees working remotely world wide and joining us from offices in San Francisco, Washington DC, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, and The Netherlands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Trade Compliance Officer for Planet Labs Germany GmbH, you will be a member of the Planet’s International Trade Compliance (ITC) team within the global Legal organization and will have the opportunity to work on issues that may have large compliance and/or financial implications for the company.&amp;nbsp; You will routinely interface with engineers, supply chain, IT, security, sales, and other local and international personnel, as well as external counsel and vendors to mitigate compliance risks and support secure and efficient global trade operations.&amp;nbsp; The ideal candidate will be a seasoned international trade compliance professional with great judgment and attention to detail, who is comfortable making independent compliance decisions and consulting with a broader compliance team, as needed for support.&amp;nbsp; As Planet’s German Trade Compliance Officer, you will serve as the face of export control for Planet’s German manufacturing operations and make a significant contribution to the legally compliant and efficient implementation of international trade regulations and global standards.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, hybrid role which will require you to work from our Berlin office or lab 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You’ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as German Trade Compliance Officer and a trusted advisor to Planet’s legal and business teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In coordination with Planet’s US ITC team and Planet policy, ensuring implementation of an effective Internal Compliance Programme (ICP) aligned with expectations of BAFA and the EU-Commission with adherence to national and EU export control laws and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as subject matter expert and ensuring company activities comply with national and EU export control laws and regulations, including but not limited to EU Dual-Use Regulation, German Foreign Trade Law (AWG/AWV), and the War Weapons Control Act (as applicable).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining Planet’s registration in ELAN-K2 portal and preparing/submitting applications for individual and global authorizations in support of Planet business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying and overseeing compliant use of German or EU General Authorizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owning full lifecycle/authorization management related to German/EU authorizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing/documenting German/EU classification analysis applicable to Planet products and services and making licensing determinations to support business operations, including tracking new technology developments within the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In consultation with the US ITC team, ensuring company operations comply with any applicable U.S. re-export controls (e.g., EAR/ITAR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advising the business on international trade compliance requirements and developing strategic compliance plans to meet business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interfacing with outside counsel/consultants related to non-US global trade controls.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as interface with German and EU governmental bodies in support of Planet trade compliance initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing and providing guidance on international trade compliance terms and conditions in proposals/contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing/filing international trade compliance requests with German/EU authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing/approving visitor requests to ensure adherence to compliance requirements and Planet policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing technology control plans to support compliant working of business operations and manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing and conducting compliance trainings for employees to raise awareness of international trade compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing the compliance review/gating process for international shipments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drafting and preparing filings for government agencies, including license applications, regulatory notifications, and scheduled reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring company compliance with other international trade laws, including as relates to applicable sanctions and embargoes and anti-bribery/anti-corruption requirements, including supporting enhanced due diligence as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously monitoring updates to export control regulations, sanctions/embargoes, and anti-bribery laws in Germany, the EU, and globally, and ensure internal processes are updated accordingly .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining record retention and organization in accordance with Planet policy and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
